<FIRST>r a PM-HelmsleyQuotes     12-13 0193</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Helmsley Quotes,0201</SECOND>
<HEAD>Helmsley Quotes</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Helmsley</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Quotes from the sentencing of Leona Helmsley:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Mrs. Helmsley:
   ``I am more humiliated and ashamed than anybody can ever imagine
that I've been found guilty of a serious crime. ... I feel like I'm
in the middle of a nightmare.''
   ``A few years ago, I lost my only son. They dug up his grave and
ripped me apart in the newspapers. I beg you, don't let me lose
Harry, too.''
   ``Our whole life has been work and each other. Please don't. We
have nothing else. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Judge John M. Walker Jr.:
   ``The scheme was for your direct benefit. You bear the full
responsibility for this scheme with all of its fraudulent
permutations.''
   ``Unlike many defendants who come before the court, you were not
driven to this crime by financial greed, rather your conduct was
the product of naked greed. Throughout its course, you persisted in
the arrogant belief that you were above the law. Moreover, since
the indictment and the trial, you have displayed no remorse or
contrition at having committed the offenses in this case.''
</TEXT>
