<HEAD>Names in the News</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MERIDIAN, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush invited Rep. G.V.
Montgomery to spend Christmas with the first family because he
wanted to make sure the unmarried Democrat didn't eat his holiday
dinner alone.
   ``That's the kind of person he is,'' said Montgomery, 69, who
has known Bush since the two came to Washington, D.C,. 23 years
