<HEAD>Retransmits a0476 to fix garbled summary line</HEAD>
<HEAD>Fire at Michael Jackson's Giraffe Barn Causes $300,000 in Damage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A giraffe barn on pop music
superstar Michael Jackson's ranch went up in flames, but the
animals were evacuated safely, authorities said.
   Firefighters on Tuesday also kept flames from reaching a nearby
animal compound and chimpanzee house at the ranch in the Santa Ynez
Mountains, northwest of Santa Barbara, officials said.
   When firefighters reached the remote ranch, the barn was
destroyed and the three giraffes kept there already were evacuated,
said Capt. Charlie Johnson, Santa Barbara County Fire Department
spokesman.
   Jackson, whose menagerie includes a chimpanzee named Bubbles,
ostriches, llamas and boa constrictors, was not at the ranch at the
time, said a spokesman for the singer.
   The blaze left an estimated $300,000 in damage.
   The cause of the fire was under investigation, but it was
believed to have been accidentally ignited, Johnson said.
</TEXT>
