<FIRST>r a PM-BRF--PublishersNamed     12-13 0150</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Publishers Named,0153</SECOND>
<HEAD>Publishers Named For Pittsburgh, Ohio Papers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John Robinson Block and William Block Jr. will
become co-publishers of the Pittsburgh Post-Gazette Jan. 1., the
third generation of their family to lead the newspaper.
   The two also will co-publish The Blade in Toledo, Ohio, another
publication of Blade Communications Inc., parent company of the
Post-Gazette, it was announced Tuesday.
   They succeed William Block, 74, who is retiring as publisher of
the Post-Gazette and The Blade. He will continue as chairman of PG
Publishing Co. and of Blade Communications.
   John Robinson Block and William Block Jr. are grandsons of Paul
Block, who consolidated the Pittsburgh Post and the Pittsburgh
Gazette-Times into the Post-Gazette in 1927.
   John Robinson Block, 35, serves as assistant publisher of the
Post-Gazette. William Block Jr., 45, served as publisher of The
Daily Register in Shrewsbury, N.J., and is president of PG
Publishing.
