<HEAD>12-Year-Old Charged with Shooting Playmate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 12-year-old boy accused of shooting his
10-year-old friend has been charged with negligent homicide.
   Jeffery Fernando Miller was shot once in the chest Monday night
and his friend, unidentified because of his age, was taken into
custody Tuesday and turned over to juvenile authorities, police
said.
   Fred Warner, a deputy police chief, said the children had been
playing with an unloaded pistol.
   ``The investigation revealed that the 12-year-old had a pistol
and he was pulling the trigger pointing at different people,''
Warner said. ``There were seven children in the house ranging in
age from 7 to 14.''
   Warner said the 12-year-old put a bullet in the pistol and
pulled the trigger twice while pointing it at other children. The
third time, the gun fired and Miller was shot, he said.
   Warner said police do not know where the 12-year-old got the gun.
   The killing was the third fatal shooting by a juvenile in
Memphis since Thanksgiving. No charges were filed in the other two
incidents.
