   The citation said the knighthood was in recognition of his
outstanding contribution to British industry and commerce. It is
the 57th honorary knighthood given to an American.
   Giordano, 55, a native of New York, was chief executive of the
U.S. company Airco when the British Oxygen Company took it over in
1978.
