<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--75-CentRobbery     12-13 0187</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--75-Cent Robbery,0193</SECOND>
<HEAD>75-Cent Robbery Yields 20-Year Sentence</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AMARILLO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who tried to steal 75 cents from an
88-year-old woman last Christmas Eve, then punched her in the face
because she didn't have more money, has been sentenced to 20 years
in prison.
   Joseph Lynn Harris' sentence for attacking Celina McMurray was
tougher than most because he had a prior conviction from a 1984
burglary, Assistant District Attorney Rebecca King said Tuesday.
   Harris had pleaded guilty to robbing Ms. McMurray.
   During sentencing Tuesday, Ms. McMurray told District Judge Sam
Kiser that Harris and his co-defendant, Ricky Wilson, beat her,
tied her to a chair and ransacked her apartment.
   She said the men said they had been sent by the landlord to fix
her stove. She said she knew their story wasn't true, but let them
in anyway.
   The men threatened to kill her if she didn't give them all her
money, Ms. McMurray testified.
   A neighbor called police, and officers arrived soon enough to
catch the men in the apartment.
   Wilson received probation because he had no criminal record, Ms.
King said.
</TEXT>
