<DOCNO> AP891213-0156 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-12-13-89 2003EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a AM-People-Shriver     12-13 0103</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Shriver,0106</SECOND>
<HEAD>It's a Girl for Shriver and Schwarzenegger</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It's a girl for news anchor Maria Shriver and
Hollywood muscleman Arnold Schwarzenegger.
   The baby was delivered early Wednesday at an undisclosed area
hospital, according to the couple's publicist Charlotte Parker.
Schwarzenegger was with his wife when the child was born.
   ``All three are very healthy,'' said Parker, who was unable to
provide specifics on the infant's name, weight or time of birth.
   Ms. Shriver, 33, is an NBC-TV news anchor. Schwarzenegger, 41,
an Austrian-born former Mr. Universe, has starred in such films as
``The Terminator'' and ``Red Heat.''
