<FILEID>AP-NR-12-13-89 0848EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u f BC-BritishStocks     12-13 0173</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-British Stocks,0183</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Stocks Sharply Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were sharply higher Wednesday as the
market responded to Wall Street's rise Tuesday and continued
strength in the newly privatized water company stocks.
   Dealers reported strong two-way business, particularly in the
quality blue-chip stocks.
   ``When we get a line of stock it is fairly easy to place, which
shows there is still a fair amount of confidence in the market,''
one dealer said.
   At midday, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index
was up 17.5 points, or 0.7 percent, at 2,381.0 points, also its
session high.
   The market opened 15.7 points higher, then temporarily drifted
lower before recovering its upward momentum.
   ``The market still looks fairly resilient around current
levels,'' one dealer said.
   Dealers said banking and oil stocks were particularly strong.
   Also, the shares in the 10 privatized water companies, which
began trading Tuesday, continued to perform solidly Wednesday
morning.
   Volume came to a healthy 323.6 million shares at midday,
compared with 545.1 million shares at the same time Tuesday.
</TEXT>
