<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Stocks End Sharply Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stocks closed higher in moderate trading on
London's Stock Exchange Wednesday, as the market took its cue from
a buoyant Wall Street.
   At the close, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index
was up 22.7 points, or 1 percent, at 2,386.2.
   The Financial Times 30-share index gained 18.6 points to 1,880.1
at the close. The Financial Times 500-share index rose 11.81 points
to 1,295.60.
   Volume amounted to 531.8 million shares, of which around 30
percent reflected trading in new shares in the 10 water authorities
of England and Wales. Total volume was well below Tuesday's 800.4
million shares, when the water shares began trading.
   Trading quieted down in the water shares, which ended narrowly
mixed.
   At the end of the London trading day, the Dow Jones industrial
average was up 11.10 at 2,763.23 in New York.
   Reuters PLC was among the biggest gainers Wednesday, with its
shares surging 66 pence ($1.06) to 10.88 pounds ($17.52).
</TEXT>
