<FIRST>r f AM-GTE-HSN     12-13 0161</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-GTE-HSN,0168</SECOND>
<HEAD>GTE Settles with Home Shopping For $4.5 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   GTE Corp. has accepted $4.5 million from Home
Shopping Network as a cash settlement that ended a $100 million
damage award against the television retailer.
   The two sides announced in November they had reached an
undisclosed settlement, but the dollar amount became public through
filings to the Florida Public Service Commission made by GTE's
Tampa-based subsidiary GTE Florida.
   GTE has said its legal costs exceeded the settlement. The PSC
has to determine whether those excess costs should be passed along
to rate payers or to GTE shareholders.
   HSN, based in Clearwater, Fla., had sued GTE for $1.5 billion,
claiming GTE had sold it faulty equipment and covered up the
problems. GTE later sued HSN, arguing that the company was blaming
the telephone utility for problems that were caused by poor
management.
   In August, a jury denied the HSN claim and awarded GTE a record
$100 million.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
